<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1104">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/1375.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your May 9. You are authorized to advise Americans who have recently been
                            provided with transportation and assistance at the expense of this
                            Government to reach their homes in the United States that should they
                            return to Mexico during the present disturbed conditions in that country
                            and later on be obliged to leave they should not look to this Government
                            for further assistance in the way of transportation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>